B.aun=new A.cw("Where do I find Analytics?",'Go to the Dashboard tab and tap the "Analytics" chip at the top. The Analytics view lives alongside the Overview tab on the same screen.')
B.auB=new A.cw("What is the P&L Over Time chart?","This chart tracks your cumulative profit and loss over time. A line trending upward means you're profitable \u2014 every session adds (or subtracts) from your running total. Switch between Cumulative, Weekly, Monthly, and Yearly views using the chips above the chart.")
B.auH=new A.cw("How do Analytics filters work?","Tap the filter icon (sliders) in the top-right of the screen when on the Analytics tab. You can filter by date range, display currency, country, venue type (Live/Online), and specific location. All charts and insight cards update to reflect the filtered data.")
B.au9=new A.cw("What are the Insight Cards?","Insight Cards break down your performance by different dimensions: stakes, buy-in level, game type, day of week, time of day, session length, table quality, and location. Each card shows your P&L and win rate for that segment so you can see exactly where you perform best.")
B.au_=new A.cw("What are Recommendations?","Recommendations uses Welch's t-test \u2014 a statistical method \u2014 to detect meaningful differences in your performance across conditions. For example, if your live results are significantly stronger than online, it flags that. Expand the section to see actionable suggestions.")
B.au7=new A.cw("What is Hourly Rate?","Hourly rate is your average profit per hour of play, calculated from sessions where you logged both a start and end time (or a duration). It's one of the most useful metrics for cash game players to compare across stakes and locations.")
B.a4y=s([B.aun,B.auB,B.auH,B.au9,B.au_,B.au7],t.Bt)
